Peace Marathon Race in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 25 (KCNA) -- A "peace marathon race for checking expansion of U.S. military base in Phyongthaek" was held in Phyongthaek, Kyonggi Province of south Korea on May 21, according to a news report.
 Participating in the marathon race sponsored by the Phyongthaek Measure Committee for Checking the Expansion of the U.S. Military Base were citizens of Phyongthaek and members of civic organizations, students and pupils of primary schools from different parts of South Korea.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at a rally held before the marathon race said that they expect that through the marathon race the people will realize the unreasonableness of the expansion of the U.S. military base by themselves and turn out in the struggle to defend the peace of Phyongthaek area. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The runners started from the Phyongthaek public playground, wearing letters "against expansion of U.S. military base" on their breasts and ran through the city, holding slogan boards reading "stop to forcible expropriation" in their hands and bringing to light the injustice of the expansion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the race the participants made demonstration marches and conducted various propaganda activities in different parts of the city.

Week Event of Iran-Korea Friendship in Teheran  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Teheran, May 23 (KCNA) -- A week event of Iran-Korea Friendship was held in Teheran from May 14 to 20.
 An opening ceremony was held on May 14. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display at the venue of the opening ceremony were photos of President Kim Il Sung meeting and having talks with leader Seyed Ali Khamenei, photos of leader Kim Jong Il giving on-the-spot guidance to different fields, their famous works, books and photos showing proud achievements made by the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the ceremony said that the relations between Iran and the DPRK are special relations. The bilateral relations are boosted by the resistance of the two peoples against dominationists and plunderers, struggle slogans and action against dominationists of the world, indomitable spirit and objective to defend national dignity and independence to the end. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They expressed the expectation that good achievements and experience of the two governments and the two peoples in socio-economic development would be introduced and through this the bilateral relations of friendship and cooperation would further develop during the week. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then the participants appreciated Korean film "Mangyongdae" before looking round books and photos on display. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During the event Korean films introducing Songun Korea were screened.

Fidel Castro Ruz on Boosting Cuba-Korea Relations 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Havana, May 23 (KCNA) -- Fidel Castro Ruz, first secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Cuba, president of the Council of State and president of the Council of Ministers of Cuba, stressed the need to boost the friendly and cooperative relations between the two parties and two countries of Cuba and the DPRK in the joint struggle for socialism against the U.S., noting that the two countries have supported and cooperated with each other as the countries standing in confrontation with it.
 He met with the delegation of the Workers' Party of Korea led by Kim Ki Nam, secretary of its Central Committee, on a visit to Cuba and had a talk with it in a friendly atmosphere at the Revolutionary Palace on May 22. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the meeting he recalled that the Korean people are the brave people who built modern cities and villages one can see today after the war during which everything was reduced to ashes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing full support to the proposals for national reunification put forward by the party and government of the DPRK, he hoped that Korea would be reunified at an early date. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were members of the WPK delegation, Pak Tong Chun, DPRK ambassador to Cuba, Carlos Rage Davila, member of the Political Bureau of the C. C., the Communist Party of Cuba and vice-president of the Council of State of Cuba, Fernando Ramirez, head of the International Department of the CPC Central Committee, and officials concerned.

Anniversary of Chongryon Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 25 (KCNA) -- Papers here today extend warm congratulations and compatriotic greetings to all officials of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) and Koreans in Japan who have fully demonstrated their dignity, honor and might, braving manifold difficulties and ordeals, on the occasion of the 51st anniversary of the foundation of Chongryon.
 Rodong Sinmun in a signed article says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The 51 years covered by Chongryon represent a glorious history in which it set a model of the Juche-oriented overseas compatriots movement under the leadership of President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il, a history of patriotism and loyalty in which it has remained intensely loyal to the leaders, the homeland and the people and a proud one in which it has recorded the annals of the patriotic movement with victories and glory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
 The formation of Chongryon was a brilliant embodiment of the Juche-oriented idea and leadership of the President over the overseas compatriots movement and a historic event which brought about a signal change in the movement of Koreans in Japan and their life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chongryon has creditably fulfilled its responsibility and role as the representative and defender of genuine rights and interests of the Koreans in Japan. In this course it has enjoyed unreserved love and deep trust from broad strata of compatriots. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has, at the same time, waged a vigorous struggle to achieve great national unity and national reunification, deeply aware of being part of the driving force for the movement for national reunification, strengthened the friendship with the peoples of different countries including the Japanese people and developed the relations with international organizations and other bodies, thus making big contributions to creating an international environment favorable for the movement of Koreans in Japan and national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Many countries have their compatriots overseas and their organizations in the world, but there can hardly be in any other parts of the world such overseas compatriots organization as Chongryon intensely loyal to the leader, the nation and the homeland and enthusiastic in compatriotism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No force on earth can stop Chongryon from resolutely defending the patriotic cause, remaining true to its faith and sense of obligation despite manifold difficulties and stern ordeals. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson in an editorial says that the patriotic cause of Chongryon is sure to triumph along with the socialist homeland led by Kim Jong Il.

U.S. Arrogance Ignoring UN under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 25 (KCNA) -- The U.S. arbitrary and self-opinionated action of shaking its stick and dictating at the UN has gone beyond the limit. With nothing can the U.S. justify its action of ignoring the UN and take its place.
 Rodong Sinmun says this in a signed article Thursday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the U.S. attitude toward the UN to use it as a tool for carrying out its purpose of aggression, a stage for establishing an order of hegemonic domination over the world, the article notes, and observes: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Typical examples of disregarding the UN are the U.S. imperialists' invasion of Iraq, their moves to pressurize Iran over the nuclear issue and their intensified policy of military occupation of south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. arrogant act of ignoring the UN is exerting a great influence on world peace and human civilization. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Owing to the U.S. arrogance the major principles of international relations including the UN Charter, international law, international justice and impartiality have been violated and the world plunged into confusion and disorder. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 For the U.S. to ignore the UN is as good as ignoring the world and debasing and rejecting humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In order to prevent the U.S. highhanded and arbitrary practices and establish a new fair international order in the international arena, all the countries including the UN member nations should resolutely fight against the U.S. policy of aggression, the policy of ignoring the UN. And they should enhance the authority and role of the UN as required by the new century so that the U.S. may not act at its own discretion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Those who turn their back on the people and block the trend of the times are bound to face international isolation and ruin. The U.S. is now in such a position. It had better understand its plight clearly and stop committing such criminal acts as ignoring the UN and resorting to highhanded and arbitrary practices.

Kim Yong Nam Meets Chinese Delegation 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 25 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, met and had a friendly conversation with a delegation of the Chinese People's Daily led by President Wang Chen at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on Thursday.
 Present there were Choe Chil Nam, editor-in-chief of Rodong Sinmun, and Wu Donghe, Chinese ambassador to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the occasion the head of the delegation said that while visiting various places, he witnessed successes gained by the Korean people in socialist construction under the wise guidance of General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the Sino-Korean relations of friendship and cooperation are favorably developing with each passing day under the deep concern of the top leaders of the two countries, he expressed the conviction that the Korean people under the leadership of the Workers' Party of Korea would register greater success in socialist construction.

New Kind of Cement Reinforcing Material Developed in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 25 (KCNA) -- Plastic fiber, a new kind of cement reinforcing material, has been developed in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 It is used in making quality roofing slates and ceiling boards of dwelling houses and public buildings, pipes and other building materials in proper combination with cement. The fiber is made with the help of latest fiber processing technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As its surface is very rough and has many prickles according to the microscopic examination, the plastic fiber ensures powerful adhesion with cement solution. Therefore, the plastic fiber building materials are good in quality and have a long serviceable life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In addition, the production cost of the plastic fiber building materials is nearly 50 per cent lower than that of other ones. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ho Ho Yong, a section chief of the DPRK General Bureau of Invention, told KCNA that according to the survey of international inventions and industrial patents, the plastic fiber processing technology is superior to others not only in the economic aspect but in technical features.

Korea Sports Fund Established
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 25 (KCNA) -- The Korea Sports Fund (KSF) was set up on April 12, Juche 95 (2006) as a legal body of the DPRK government for public interests.
 The KSF, situated in Puksae-dong, Moranbong District, Pyongyang, has a Standing Council and Secretariat. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its mission is to regulate and encourage financial and material donation and cooperation rendered by individual figures at home and abroad, overseas Koreans, foreigners, public bodies and organizations with the spirit of lofty patriotism and humanitarianism and on the voluntary principle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recently voluntary financial and material donation and cooperation were offered to the KSF by Koreans at home and abroad, the Hong Kong Talented Dragon Investment Co., Ltd. of China, the Wellstone Enterprise Co., Ltd. of Japan and various other foreign organizations of their own accord. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chairperson of the KSF Ri Hye Gyong, in an interview with KCNA, expressed the hope that many Koreans at home and abroad and foreign sports fans, groups and organizations would make a positive contribution to the sports development of the DPRK in the spirit of collaboration in the future, too.

Kim Jong Il Appreciates Art Performance
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 25 (KCNA) -- Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the National Defence Commission of the DPRK, appreciated a performance given by art groups of families of servicemen of KPA Units 287 and 567 who had participated in the 9th contest among art groups of families of servicemen of the KPA.
 The performers staged chorus "Song of Loyalty", vocal solo, poem reciting, janggu ensemble, chorus and story telling, folk song chorus, poem and story telling, drama based on a real story and other numbers of various genres. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They enthusiastically sang of their great pride and honor of being dependable women revolutionaries and admirable No. two Songun buglers under the loving care of Kim Jong Il and their worthwhile life and powerfully demonstrated the unshakable faith and will and revolutionary stamina and indomitable spirit of the families of the servicemen to firmly defend the headquarters of the revolution and remain true to the sacred Songun cause like a fortress devotedly safeguarding it alongside their husbands under arms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He extended high appreciation to the members of the art groups for their successful performance, expressing great satisfaction over the fact that they gave a splendid performance rich in ideological content and high in artistry as it truthfully represented important socio-political issues arising in the struggle and life of people in the era of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He also extended warm gratitude to all the performers and those families of servicemen who sincerely helped them, noting that the contests held among art groups of families of servicemen nine times clearly proved the validity and vitality of the WPK's literary and art policy on popularizing arts and strikingly demonstrated the proud feature of the new culture created in the era of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He set forth tasks which would serve as guidelines in further developing popular art activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the audience were KPA Generals Ri Myong Su, Hyon Chol Hae and Pak Jae Gyong and other general officers, Ri Yong Chol, Ri Je Gang and Ri Jae Il, first vice department directors of the C.C., WPK, Kim Yang Gon, councilor of the NDC of the DPRK, and other senior officials.
